                <Gloss>abundant</Gloss>
                <Gloss>abundantly</Gloss>
                <Gloss>greatly</Gloss>
                <Gloss>extremely</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages, the expression τὸ πλοῦτος τῆς χάριτος αὐτοῦ in {S:04900100700032} would need to be translated as ‘he is very, very kind.’ Though syntactically ὁ πλοῦτος is the nominal head of the phrase in {S:04900101800040}, semantically ὁ πλοῦτος indicates the extent of the δόξα, and δόξα, in turn, clarifies the nature of the κληρονομία.</Comments>
